npm install

bower install

npm install -g grunt-cli

sudo easy_install pip

pip install csvkit

# serve “debug” where files are not inlined
grunt serve --project PROJECT_NAME_IN_PROJECTS_FOLDER --debug

# serve to localhost:4000/projects/PROJECT_NAME
# can open build with survey.csv at localhost:4000/projects/PROJECT_NAME/build/output/
grunt serve --project PROJECT_NAME_IN_PROJECTS_FOLDER

# upload to ubiquity reading from ENV (currently hardcoded to gkhanna ubiquity)
grunt serve --project PROJECT_NAME_IN_PROJECTS_FOLDER --staging

# build to prod, copy build/index.min.html to clipboard
grunt serve —-project PROJECT_NAME_IN_PROJECTS_FOLDER --prod

#http://localhost:4000/projects/HolyLoad/build/output/


TO BUILD (WITHOUT INLINING) UPLOADING RESOURCES TO EXTERNAL HOSTING

grunt serve —project PROJECT_NAME_IN_PROJECTS_FOLDER --prod=1 --noinline

THEN UPLOAD CONTENTS OF build/resources/ TO EXTERNAL HOSTING

THEN TAKE THE ROOT URL FOR THE FILES, e.g. = https://www.google.com/evaluation/endor/blob/3ee18d15_9b77_4894_baf4_09e75122a0ac/

AND RUN
grunt serve —project PROJECT_NAME_IN_PROJECTS_FOLDER --prod=1 --noinline=https://www.google.com/evaluation/endor/blob/3ee18d15_9b77_4894_baf4_09e75122a0ac/

THEN build/index.min.html REFERENCES ALL EXTERNAL FILES WITH THAT URL
